00:26:43.510 --> 00:26:45.580
So asked, is there
any questions?

00:26:45.580 --> 00:26:48.241
They were so confused they
couldn't articulate a question.

00:26:48.241 --> 00:26:49.490
So I thought, this is serious.

00:26:49.490 --> 00:26:51.531
I erased the board, and
in the next eight minutes

00:26:51.531 --> 00:26:53.680
I managed to produce the
most brilliant explanation

00:26:53.680 --> 00:26:55.110
you can possibly imagine.

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:58.400
The whole board was covered
with equations and drawings,

00:26:58.400 --> 00:27:01.000
and I triumphantly
turnaround, thinking,

00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.820
I nailed it this
time, only to see

00:27:02.820 --> 00:27:05.600
that they look
even more confused.

00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:09.180
And they still couldn't
articulate a coherent question.

00:27:09.180 --> 00:27:10.550
So you know how it is, right?

00:27:10.550 --> 00:27:11.924
If you don't
understand something

00:27:11.924 --> 00:27:14.260
it's hard to articulate it.

00:27:14.260 --> 00:27:15.590
So I didn't know what to do.

00:27:15.590 --> 00:27:19.139
I'd used my whole arsenal
trying to explain it.

00:27:19.139 --> 00:27:21.430
But I knew that half of them
had given the right answer

00:27:21.430 --> 00:27:25.060
on that particular question, so
in a moment of despair I said,

00:27:25.060 --> 00:27:28.320
why don't you discuss
it with each other?

00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:31.540
And something happened
that I'd never seen before.

00:27:31.540 --> 00:27:33.060
I had 250 students in my class.

00:27:33.060 --> 00:27:36.429
Complete chaos broke out.

00:27:36.429 --> 00:27:37.470
They all started arguing.

00:27:37.470 --> 00:27:38.790
They forgot about me
in front of the class.

00:27:38.790 --> 00:27:39.750
I could've walked away.

00:27:39.750 --> 00:27:41.820
They would not have noticed it.

00:27:41.820 --> 00:27:45.882
And what happened is, two
minutes they figured it out.

00:27:45.882 --> 00:27:48.730
At first I thought,
how is that possible?

00:27:48.730 --> 00:27:49.656
Right?

00:27:49.656 --> 00:27:53.590
I mean, I, the expert,
have taken 10 minutes

00:27:53.590 --> 00:27:56.330
to explain it, unsuccessfully?

00:27:56.330 --> 00:27:58.740
And in just two minutes
they figured it out?

00:27:58.740 --> 00:28:01.930
Imagine you're Mary and John
sitting next to each other.

00:28:01.930 --> 00:28:04.450
Mary has the right
answer, John does not.

00:28:04.450 --> 00:28:06.380
On average, Mary's
more likely convince

00:28:06.380 --> 00:28:08.390
John than the other way around.

00:28:08.390 --> 00:28:10.960
But the key point is this.

00:28:10.960 --> 00:28:13.200
Mary is more likely
to convince John

00:28:13.200 --> 00:28:15.570
than Professor Mazur
in front of the class,

00:28:15.570 --> 00:28:18.700
because she has only
recently learned it.

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:20.300
She still knows what
the difficulties

00:28:20.300 --> 00:28:21.508
are to the beginning learner.

00:28:21.508 --> 00:28:24.120
As Professor Mazur learned
