McTighe in their book,

00:52:59.050 --> 00:53:00.540
"Understanding by Design."

00:53:00.540 --> 00:53:03.440
So why not ask ourselves,
what are the desired

00:53:03.440 --> 00:53:06.880
outcomes of this
educational discourse?

00:53:06.880 --> 00:53:10.150
And you have to formulate
those with action verbs

00:53:10.150 --> 00:53:12.651
rather than saying, content
topic one, topic two, topic

00:53:12.651 --> 00:53:13.150
three.

00:53:13.150 --> 00:53:14.070
You have to ask
yourself, what do

00:53:14.070 --> 00:53:17.010
I want my student to be able
to do after taking this course,

00:53:17.010 --> 00:53:23.214
or after finishing this year
in school or in college?

00:53:23.214 --> 00:53:24.880
A lot of my colleagues
really like that,

00:53:24.880 --> 00:53:26.713
but they have a lot of
difficulty with that.

00:53:26.713 --> 00:53:29.240
They will say, well,
after taking this course,

00:53:29.240 --> 00:53:33.730
you will be able to understand
Topic A, Topic B, Topic

00:53:33.730 --> 00:53:36.690
C. The content is so ingrained.

00:53:36.690 --> 00:53:39.380
Anyway, once you have
formulated outcomes,

00:53:39.380 --> 00:53:42.730
you can ask yourself, what am
I going to accept as evidence?

00:53:42.730 --> 00:53:44.181
So you think about
the assessment.

00:53:44.181 --> 00:53:46.180
And then, what am I going
to do in the classroom

00:53:46.180 --> 00:53:48.570
to maximize those outcomes?

00:53:48.570 --> 00:53:51.860
And I think in education we
haven't done enough of that.

