what the right answer is,

01:01:23.130 --> 01:01:26.270
but she would not be
able to explain it.

01:01:26.270 --> 01:01:27.360
Kids start talking.

01:01:27.360 --> 01:01:30.620
You see this chaos, and then
they raise their flashcards

01:01:30.620 --> 01:01:33.029
again and you see an
overwhelming shift

01:01:33.029 --> 01:01:33.945
to the correct answer.

01:01:35.650 --> 01:01:38.020
And then she said--
and I was really

01:01:38.020 --> 01:01:40.350
wondering, how is she going
to handle this-- she says,

01:01:40.350 --> 01:01:42.290
are there any remaining-- oh no.

01:01:42.290 --> 01:01:44.500
First she shows an explanation.

01:01:44.500 --> 01:01:47.660
It would be the instructor
in New Delhi giving

01:01:47.660 --> 01:01:48.820
the explanation.

01:01:48.820 --> 01:01:51.140
And then the social
worker in the classroom

01:01:51.140 --> 01:01:53.579
said, does anybody have
any remaining questions?

01:01:53.579 --> 01:01:55.120
I thought, how is
she going to answer

01:01:55.120 --> 01:01:57.550
that given that she
doesn't know any physics?

01:01:57.550 --> 01:01:59.930
One student raises
his hand and says,

01:01:59.930 --> 01:02:02.492
well I don't understand why
blah, blah, blah and so on.

01:02:02.492 --> 01:02:04.950
So she says, is there anybody
who knows the answer to that?

01:02:04.950 --> 01:02:08.040
She just plays the kids
out against one another.

01:02:08.040 --> 01:02:10.020
And if there's an issue
that remains unresolved

01:02:10.020 --> 01:02:10.890
she takes it down.

01:02:10.890 --> 01:02:15.030
It gets sent to the mother
office, the main office in New

01:02:15.030 --> 01:02:17.710
Delhi, and they resolve
it the next time around.

01:02:17.710 --> 01:02:18.880
Fantastic.

01:02:18.880 --> 01:02:20.340
I always thought
that the teacher

01:02:20.340 --> 01:02:25.440
had to be here if
the kids were there.

01:02:25.440 --> 01:02:28.840
But the balance is the
other way around there.

01:02:28.840 --> 01:02:32.550
