01:07:42.410 --> 01:07:45.665
The homework consists not
only about watching a lecture

01:07:45.665 --> 01:07:49.490
or reading a book but
also applying some.

01:07:49.490 --> 01:07:50.890
Learning is a
scaffolded process.

01:07:50.890 --> 01:07:52.850
You don't go from
not knowing anything

01:07:52.850 --> 01:07:54.380
to knowing everything
in one step.

01:07:54.380 --> 01:07:56.350
You learn a little bit,
and a little bit more.

01:07:56.350 --> 01:07:59.240
So the reading primes
the pump, or the watching

01:07:59.240 --> 01:08:01.200
the lecture primes the pump.

01:08:01.200 --> 01:08:03.880
The in-class activity pushes the
students a little bit higher,

01:08:03.880 --> 01:08:05.963
and then there are other
activities, some of which

01:08:05.963 --> 01:08:07.670
can be done at
home, that continue

01:08:07.670 --> 01:08:09.690
to reinforce the process.

01:08:09.690 --> 01:08:12.519
It's really a
scaffolded process.

